{
  "text": "The same limitations apply to numerical methods developed recently to compute rate functions efficiently. Except for the direct Monte Carlo method used here, all methods, including cloning [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and importance sampling [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , work by reweighting trajectories exponentially with time in a normal way. In this sense, the model proposed here should serve as an ideal toy model to develop new analytical and numerical methods that are applicable to physical systems with anomalous large deviations, including the many non-Markovian and disordered processes mentioned in the introduction.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "18056819",
    "[CITATION_2]": "13704339",
    "[CITATION_3]": "13705501",
    "[CITATION_4]": "60459112",
